> This recipe calls for only one or two tortillas which means you will have quite a
> few leftover! We hate waste so are always thinking of ways to use left-over
> ingredients. One suggestion is to make oven baked tortilla chips (healthier than
> deep fried but still delicious!) You can brush them with oil and then make them
> savory with a sprinkling of salt and some paprika or sweet with cinnamon and
> sugar. A few minutes in a hot oven and voila!

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Peel and very finely dice the
@garlic{1%clove} and the @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Remove the core from
the @green pepper{1}(cored and chopped into roughly 1cm chunks). Drain and
thoroughly rinse the @mixed beans{1%400g can}. Peel and chop the
@potato{1}(peeled and chopped into ½cm cubes).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot add
the @minced beef{150%g} with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until just
browned, then remove to the side for later.

> Tip: If you have a small pan, cook the meat in batches to stop it stewing.

Add the chopped pepper into the hot pan and fry for around ~{4-5%minutes}. Once
the pepper is browned off, remove from the pan and keep to the side with the
meat.

Turn the heat down to medium-low and add @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}. Add the garlic
and onion and gently cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft. Add the potato and cook
for another ~{2%minutes}.

Add the @Mexican spice{1/2%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} and stir for
~{1%minute}.

> Tip: Use less of the Mexican spice if you want less heat.

Add the beef mince and the mixed beans. Lastly, add the green pepper and the
@tomato passata{1%small carton}.

Add the @beef stock pot{1} together with @water{900%ml}. Bring the soup to a
gentle simmer (i.e. it should not be bubbling very vigorously). Gently cook the
soup for around ~{10%minutes}.

Rub a very light coating of @olive oil{} onto both sides of your
@super soft tortillas with whole wheat{1}. Slice the tortilla into long strips
(1cm thick), season with salt and pepper and place in the oven. Cook until
really crispy (about ~{4-5%minutes}) but watch them like a hawk as they'll easily
burn!

Just before serving the soup stir through a couple of tbsp of
@coriander{2%sprigs}(chopped). Top each bowl with a dollop of @sour cream{2%tbsp},
a little more chopped coriander and some of your crispy tortilla chips. Get
slurping!